body:
You can find a single document using the [collection.findOne()](collection.findOne)
method.

The following [Atlas Function](atlas-functions) snippet finds a single
document from the `items` collection that has a `quantity` greater
than or equal to `25`:

```javascript
const query = { "quantity": { "$gte": 25 } };
const projection = {
 "title": 1,
 "quantity": 1,
}

return itemsCollection.findOne(query, projection)
  .then(result => {
    if(result) {
      console.log(`Successfully found document: ${result}.`);
    } else {
      console.log("No document matches the provided query.");
    }
    return result;
  })
  .catch(err => console.error(`Failed to find document: ${err}`));
```

